1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 12=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:00:50,670 --> 00:00:51,510
Chen!

4
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:55,840
Are you alright?

5
00:01:07,590 --> 00:01:08,680
Chen Youxi!

6
00:01:09,870 --> 00:01:10,710
Watch out!

7
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:41,640
Chen!

8
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:42,710
Chen Youxi!

9
00:01:42,710 --> 00:01:44,120
- Chen!
- Chen!

10
00:01:45,310 --> 00:01:46,150
Be careful!

11
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:52,000
This thing is too heavy.
We can't push it.

12
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,640
Chen Youxi!

13
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:59,510
Chen, shout if you hear me!

14
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,040
Chen!

15
00:02:01,430 --> 00:02:02,310
Chen Youxi!

16
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,320
Chen!

17
00:02:13,430 --> 00:02:14,750
Chen Youxi!

18
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:49,750
Chen!

19
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:54,080
Chubby! Chubby!

20
00:02:55,750 --> 00:02:56,776
I think I heard something.

21
00:03:04,630 --> 00:03:05,630
He's still alive.

22
00:03:05,710 --> 00:03:06,630
If there's sound,

23
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:08,470
there must be space underneath.

24
00:03:08,910 --> 00:03:09,870
Let's think of a way.

25
00:03:09,870 --> 00:03:10,740
But it's too heavy.

26
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:11,650
How do we move it?

27
00:03:15,150 --> 00:03:16,000
We're finished.

28
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:17,960
We're in this mess again.

29
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:19,560
Huang Long took the treasure.

30
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:21,080
And Chen got trapped inside.

31
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:22,590
How are we supposed to get out now?

32
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:23,806
Can you stop that nonsense

33
00:03:23,817 --> 00:03:24,840
and say something useful?

34
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:26,430
We lost both Chen and the treasure.

35
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:27,280
Say that again.

36
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,240
Stop arguing.

37
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,240
Huang Long

38
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,680
keeps blowing things up.

39
00:03:37,470 --> 00:03:38,310
Blowing?

40
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:47,960
Ms. He,

41
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:49,000
what are you doing?

42
00:03:49,906 --> 00:03:51,389
The only way to move that huge sphere

43
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,430
is with explosives.

44
00:03:52,710 --> 00:03:54,030
Didn't Huang Long bring some?

45
00:04:15,910 --> 00:04:16,750
Come on.

46
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:23,760
Give it to me.

47
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:23,000
What's this?

48
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:24,200
Camphor.

49
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:25,950
It clears the mind

50
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:26,920
and repels insects.

51
00:05:32,070 --> 00:05:33,000
Where are we?

52
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:35,840
No idea.

53
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:37,680
Where are the others?

54
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:39,160
Above us.

55
00:05:43,289 --> 00:05:44,502
Where did that torch come from?

56
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:46,360
I found it in a corner. It still works.

57
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,240
Why not use a flashlight?

58
00:05:48,390 --> 00:05:49,669
The torch smoke stings the eyes.

59
00:05:51,630 --> 00:05:53,390
We don't know
what's going on down here

60
00:05:53,390 --> 00:05:54,680
or how long we'll be stuck.

61
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:56,270
Saving battery can't hurt.

62
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,560
You're just exploring a tomb.

63
00:06:25,430 --> 00:06:28,270
Yet you're split into factions,
plotting against each other.

64
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,160
What kind of boss do you have?

65
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:33,480
He made Huang Long
and me check each other

66
00:06:33,950 --> 00:06:35,510
to maximize his own interests.

67
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,390
Nothing wrong with that.

68
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,830
You've got quite the mindset.

69
00:06:41,630 --> 00:06:42,830
Huang Long took your item.

70
00:06:42,830 --> 00:06:43,670
What will you do?

71
00:06:46,310 --> 00:06:47,480
He really thinks

72
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,950
he got something valuable.

73
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,310
In that four-sided coffin earlier,

74
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:52,480
aside from the box,

75
00:06:52,796 --> 00:06:54,576
there wasn't even a trace
of the tomb owner.

76
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:57,920
I think it was probably
a fake main hall.

77
00:06:58,896 --> 00:07:00,349
Then why were you fighting me for it?

78
00:07:01,870 --> 00:07:03,680
The box had an eyeball pattern on it.

79
00:07:04,070 --> 00:07:05,800
There might be clues inside.

80
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:08,310
Huang Long must think

81
00:07:08,430 --> 00:07:09,870
it's the tomb owner's coffin.

82
00:07:10,630 --> 00:07:11,630
That's what I thought.

83
00:07:11,870 --> 00:07:13,800
Huang Long shouldn't get
so excited over a box.

84
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:16,270
So, your boss gave him
special instructions.

85
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:17,750
He doesn't trust you at all.

86
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,430
Between people,

87
00:07:20,510 --> 00:07:22,040
there's hardly any trust to begin with.

88
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:24,270
He told Huang Long separately

89
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:26,006
to keep me in check because he feared

90
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,406
I might have other intentions.

91
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:29,160
But Huang Long is so stupid.

92
00:07:29,476 --> 00:07:31,322
He believed that was
what we were looking for.

93
00:07:34,070 --> 00:07:34,910
Chubby.

94
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:37,760
Chubby!

95
00:07:42,070 --> 00:07:42,920
It's open.

96
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:43,880
Let's go.

97
00:07:44,190 --> 00:07:45,030
Slow down.

98
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:53,040
Your boss distrusts you so much,

99
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,000
yet you still help him search?

100
00:07:55,458 --> 00:07:56,655
Do you trust your team so much

101
00:07:56,666 --> 00:07:58,310
that you don't guard
against them at all?

102
00:07:58,310 --> 00:07:59,150
Of course.

103
00:07:59,870 --> 00:08:01,190
Chubby and I are like brothers.

104
00:08:01,343 --> 00:08:02,600
We've risked our lives together.

105
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,440
He's my brother.

106
00:08:05,830 --> 00:08:07,830
So, He Shutong is your brother too?

107
00:08:12,630 --> 00:08:14,390
Huang Long doesn't know
what to look for.

108
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,680
But you do, right?

109
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,480
Don't you think

110
00:08:19,491 --> 00:08:20,964
that topic change was a little abrupt?

111
00:08:22,870 --> 00:08:23,710
Lu.

112
00:08:24,530 --> 00:08:25,390
Lu!

113
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,320
Enough.

114
00:08:26,390 --> 00:08:27,950
I think we must get out first.

115
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,939
Only by finding the real main hall

116
00:08:29,950 --> 00:08:31,480
and figuring out who the tomb owner is

117
00:08:31,506 --> 00:08:32,670
can we know what that pattern

118
00:08:32,670 --> 00:08:33,840
has to do with this place.

119
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:35,350
Then, we'll find

120
00:08:35,750 --> 00:08:37,480
the answer to breaking the curse.

121
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,790
Look up.

122
00:08:40,870 --> 00:08:41,843
A phoenix pearl pattern,

123
00:08:41,854 --> 00:08:43,720
just like the one we saw
on the coffin earlier.

124
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:45,960
The form and craftsmanship are the same.

125
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:47,150
I saw the phoenix.

126
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:49,150
I know everything you said.

127
00:08:49,150 --> 00:08:50,480
Tell me something I don't know.

128
00:08:51,150 --> 00:08:51,990
For example,

129
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,200
where the exit is.

130
00:09:16,630 --> 00:09:17,470
Why stay behind me?

131
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:20,390
Are you afraid I'll ambush you?

132
00:09:21,630 --> 00:09:23,080
How many tombs have you entered?

133
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:27,670
That topic change was even more abrupt.

134
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:30,840
Just follow me.

135
00:09:42,870 --> 00:09:43,720
Take it.

136
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:46,200
Is this your first tomb?

137
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:48,200
No way.

138
00:09:49,150 --> 00:09:52,510
But this is my first Chinese tomb.

139
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:55,580
What's the difference
between Chinese and foreign tombs?

140
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,670
They follow different Feng Shui systems.

141
00:09:58,440 --> 00:10:00,510
Western tombs are smaller in scale.

142
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:01,600
Fewer burial goods.

143
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:03,422
The chance of finding something valuable

144
00:10:03,433 --> 00:10:04,240
is very small.

145
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:06,270
Because of religious traditions,

146
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:08,035
after people in the West die,

147
00:10:08,046 --> 00:10:09,390
they either go to heaven or hell.

148
00:10:09,390 --> 00:10:11,030
They value the present life.

149
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,150
Good things aren't buried in tombs.

150
00:10:18,390 --> 00:10:19,230
Empty.

151
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:21,840
It should be here.

152
00:10:23,550 --> 00:10:24,883
Why did you enter this profession?

153
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:27,240
I studied archeology in college.

154
00:10:27,550 --> 00:10:28,510
At Panier University.

155
00:10:29,270 --> 00:10:30,240
The one overseas?

156
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,529
They sent me an invitation last year

157
00:10:32,540 --> 00:10:34,360
to be a visiting scholar,
but I declined.

158
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,120
Why?

159
00:10:36,790 --> 00:10:38,030
What would I say there?

160
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:39,600
How to use the Luoyang shovel?

161
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:40,870
How to locate tombs?

162
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:43,480
Teaching foreigners to dig Chinese tombs

163
00:10:43,670 --> 00:10:44,910
would bring terrible karma.

164
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:46,960
Even though you donated everything,

165
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:49,200
deep down you're still an adventurer.

166
00:10:49,510 --> 00:10:50,440
Why?

167
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:53,240
You don't enter tombs for money.

168
00:10:53,510 --> 00:10:55,270
You just want to satisfy your curiosity

169
00:10:55,270 --> 00:10:56,323
and thirst for adventure.

170
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,510
Like little boys exploring caves.

171
00:10:58,750 --> 00:11:00,596
The more afraid they are,
the more they go in.

172
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:02,630
A kindred spirit.

173
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,000
Then why do you do it?

174
00:11:05,510 --> 00:11:07,200
Of course, I came to meet you.

175
00:11:07,510 --> 00:11:09,440
I'm your super fan.

176
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:12,630
What fan?

177
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:13,960
You're my idol.

178
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:15,920
I believe that.

179
00:11:16,646 --> 00:11:17,779
After we get out of the tomb,

180
00:11:17,790 --> 00:11:19,606
I'll take you to Beixinqiao
for stewed offal.

181
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:20,560
What?

182
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:22,000
Stewed offal.

183
00:11:25,270 --> 00:11:26,110
Offal.

184
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,660
I'll explain after we leave the tomb.

185
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:35,840
It's open.

186
00:11:53,270 --> 00:11:54,670
Huang, the blast cleared it.

187
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:55,696
We can see the surface.

188
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:57,423
Find a sturdy spot

189
00:11:57,434 --> 00:11:58,480
and set up the rope ladder.

190
00:11:58,480 --> 00:11:59,320
Yes.

191
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:00,280
Shan,

192
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:01,390
take some men up first.

193
00:12:01,390 --> 00:12:03,120
Drive the vehicle to the nearest point.

194
00:12:03,150 --> 00:12:03,990
Alright.

195
00:12:04,150 --> 00:12:04,990
Dazhuang,

196
00:12:05,030 --> 00:12:06,703
take the brothers
and move these items up.

197
00:12:06,910 --> 00:12:08,000
Don't get too excited.

198
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:08,910
Be careful.

199
00:12:08,910 --> 00:12:09,840
- Yes.
- Sure.

200
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:11,750
Huzi, Xing,

201
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:13,200
you two bring up the rear.

202
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:25,000
Those jerks actually blasted it open.

203
00:12:31,820 --> 00:12:32,670
Ms. He.

204
00:12:32,790 --> 00:12:34,440
I think

205
00:12:34,550 --> 00:12:36,080
we must handle this

206
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:37,180
very carefully.

207
00:12:37,191 --> 00:12:39,200
There are so many people
with guns and explosives.

208
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:41,030
The three of us are unarmed.

209
00:12:41,030 --> 00:12:42,150
Look at you, so cowardly.

210
00:12:42,270 --> 00:12:44,030
If we can't do it openly,
we do it secretly.

211
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:45,080
Right, secretly.

212
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:46,630
If the treasures in this tomb

213
00:12:46,630 --> 00:12:48,320
are really like Huang said,

214
00:12:48,390 --> 00:12:50,270
we'll be rich for life.

215
00:12:50,630 --> 00:12:51,790
So many treasures here.

216
00:12:54,750 --> 00:12:55,590
Who?

217
00:13:10,630 --> 00:13:11,630
No one.

218
00:13:11,630 --> 00:13:13,191
I think you've been in this tomb so long

219
00:13:13,202 --> 00:13:14,842
that your eyes
are playing tricks on you.

220
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:22,360
This one is gold.

221
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,600
How much is this worth?

222
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:25,750
What are you planning?

223
00:13:26,510 --> 00:13:29,320
If we can't take the big ones,
take a small one.

224
00:13:30,030 --> 00:13:31,150
Huang won't know.

225
00:13:31,750 --> 00:13:32,630
Don't keep it all.

226
00:13:32,630 --> 00:13:33,510
Give me half later.

227
00:13:33,510 --> 00:13:34,350
Deal.

228
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:43,560
Xing?

229
00:13:44,870 --> 00:13:45,710
Xing?

230
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:50,840
Xing?

231
00:14:20,390 --> 00:14:21,230
Commander Chen,

232
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:22,630
tell me.

233
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:25,320
Why are the two tomb chambers identical?

234
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:32,030
What's going on?

235
00:14:32,550 --> 00:14:33,729
Aren't they exactly the same?

236
00:14:34,150 --> 00:14:35,309
If we keep walking like this,

237
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:36,390
where will we end up?

238
00:14:51,270 --> 00:14:52,130
Huang,

239
00:14:52,150 --> 00:14:53,240
most of the stuff is here.

240
00:14:54,030 --> 00:14:55,480
Rest. Wait for the vehicle.

241
00:14:57,790 --> 00:14:58,696
Is anyone still inside?

242
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:00,670
Huzi and Xing are still inside.

243
00:15:00,790 --> 00:15:02,840
But we didn't see them come up.

244
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:05,160
Give it to me.

245
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:07,200
This Guanyin statue has a bumpy head.

246
00:15:07,630 --> 00:15:08,910
You thought it was a burial item?

247
00:15:08,910 --> 00:15:10,390
- It's a Yuan item.
- Lu.

248
00:15:10,630 --> 00:15:11,600
Here, take this.

249
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,440
Why are you giving me this?

250
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:16,270
For self-defense, you fool.

251
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:18,550
I don't know how to use it. You take it.

252
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:19,480
Ms. He,

253
00:15:19,550 --> 00:15:20,960
teach him how to use the gun.

254
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:22,960
Watch carefully.

255
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:25,510
This is the safety.

256
00:15:26,270 --> 00:15:27,270
This is the magazine.

257
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:31,000
When aiming, align the three points.

258
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:32,840
Keep the butt close to your shoulder.

259
00:15:36,510 --> 00:15:37,350
Here.

260
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:39,030
The safety is on.

261
00:15:41,790 --> 00:15:42,630
Like this.

262
00:15:43,030 --> 00:15:43,960
All their explosives

263
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:45,320
are on Shan.

264
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:46,790
In a moment, you two

265
00:15:46,790 --> 00:15:48,600
will draw the others away from him.

266
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,030
Leave him to me. I'll handle him.

267
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:51,440
Listen, Lu Di.

268
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:52,510
This isn't a joke.

269
00:15:52,550 --> 00:15:54,003
Stay close to Ms. He. Don't get lost.

270
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:56,200
Let's move.

271
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:41,820
♪A tiny ark sails;
the sky opens its eyes♪

272
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:47,180
♪Stillness in motion,
the earth plays its chord♪

273
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:52,820
♪A leaf falls;
we cross through time and space♪

274
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:59,970
♪In a blink, all things rest
upon our hands♪

275
00:17:00,530 --> 00:17:11,550
♪La la♪

276
00:17:18,300 --> 00:17:20,290
♪No line divides the border♪

277
00:17:20,730 --> 00:17:23,070
♪Nothing limits your performance♪

278
00:17:23,070 --> 00:17:25,440
♪Everything shows perfect harmony♪

279
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:28,130
♪Love circles the sky,
the earth, and our faith♪

280
00:17:29,630 --> 00:17:31,340
♪Hey hey hey♪

281
00:17:32,670 --> 00:17:34,490
♪Hey hey hey♪

282
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:38,140
♪Hey hey♪

283
00:17:38,290 --> 00:17:39,290
♪Hey hey♪

284
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:41,830
♪Hey hey♪

285
00:17:43,460 --> 00:17:47,660
♪Step into the galaxy of colors♪

286
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:51,960
♪Stars connect our hearts as one♪

287
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:56,460
